definitions.definition: The direction of the earth's rotation , specifically 90°.
examples: Portsmouth is to the east of Southampton.
We live in the east of the country.
The sun rises in the east .
The levanter wind is in/from the east .

definitions.definition: The eastern region or area; the inhabitants thereof.
In a church: the direction of the altar and chancel ; the direction faced by the priest when celebrating ad orientem .

main_definition: The direction of the earth's rotation , specifically 90°.
secondary_definitions: The eastern region or area; the inhabitants thereof. [circa 1300]
( ecclesiastical ) In a church: the direction of the altar and chancel ; the direction faced by the priest when celebrating ad orientem .
